Name: INLOADER\_ACC\_FAIL
Description: Generated by InLoader when creation of an InReport for an incoming report has failed
Parameters: Packet identifier of report and identifier of reason for the creation failure

Name: INLOADER\_INV\_DEST
Description: Generated by InLoader when it receives a report with an invalid destination
Parameters: Packet identifier of report and invalid destination

Name: OUTFACTORY\_FAIL
Description: Generated when an attempt to retrieve a report from the OutFactory has failed
Parameters: Type, subtype and discriminant of the report whose generation failed

Name: SNDPCKT\_INV\_DEST
Description: Generated by Send Packet Procedure when it finds an invalid destination in an OutComponent
Parameters: Type, subtype and discriminant of the report with the invalid destination and the invalid destination
